Bellzone Mining Plc (BZM)  will start iron
ore production in the Guinean town of Forecariah in March
2012, Chief Executive Officer Nik Zuks said on state-owned
Radio Television Guineenne yesterday.  A feasibility study at the site, 100 kilometers (62 miles)
from the capital, Conakry, has been conducted, he told the
broadcaster following a meeting with President  Alpha Conde .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ougna Camara in Conakry via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story: Antony Sguazzin
at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 